# Repositories Layer (Data Access Layer)
#
# Contains all SQLite database query functions, one file per entity:
#   userRepository.js         — CRUD for the users table
#   doctorRepository.js       — CRUD for the doctors table
#   vendorRepository.js       — CRUD for the vendors table
#   appointmentRepository.js  — CRUD for the appointments table
#   orderRepository.js        — CRUD for the orders table
#   chatRepository.js         — CRUD for the messages table
#
# Rule: Repositories must:
#   - Be the ONLY layer that calls db.run, db.get, db.all
#   - Return raw DB row objects or arrays
#   - Throw errors on DB failures
#   - Contain zero business logic
#
# This layer is the "M" in MVC (Model / Data Access).
# Replacing SQLite with PostgreSQL in future only requires changes here.
# Populated in: Milestone 5 (Repository Layer)
